===Etymology===
From {{etyl|frm|en}} {{term|paragraphe|lang=frm}} from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|paragraphus||sign for start of a new section of discourse|lang=la}} " from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|παράγραφος|lang=grc}}, from {{term|παρά||beside|lang=grc}} and {{term|γράφω||I write|lang=grc}}.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# A passage in text that is about a different subject from the preceding text, marked by commencing on a new line, the first line sometimes being indented.
# {{context|originally|lang=en}} A mark or note set in the [[margin]] to call attention to something in the [[text]], such as a change of subject.

